#!/usr/bin/perl -w
use strict;
use warnings;
use Spork;
our $VERSION = '0.19';

use lib 'lib';
Spork->new->load_hub->command->process(@ARGV);

__END__

=head1 NAME

spork - The Spork Command Line Utility

=head1 USAGE

    > mkdir my-slideshow
    > cd my-slideshow
    > spork -new
    > spork -make
    > spork -start

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Spork is a Perl module for creating standalone HTML slideshows from Kwiki
markup.

